<HEADLINE>
HISTORY LIMITS RE-CREATIONS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ You be Siskel, he'll be Ebert, we'll just spit out
the truth:
</P>
<P>
   Steve Prefontaine would even agree that, within reason,
</P>
<P>
   Billy Crudup's performance in ``Without Limits'' is more on
track than Jared Leto's fake hair-and-mustache job in ``Pre.''...
</P>
<P>
   ``Pre'' may have been more accurate, but ``Without Limits'' was
more believable, thanks to Donald Sutherland, too....
</P>
<P>
   The latter even gets away _ somehow _ with using NBC's Charlie
Jones and Frank Shorter on the call of the 5,000 meters from the
'72 Munich Games. Remember, ABC covered the real deal and Shorter
competed in (and won) that Olympic marathon shortly after
Prefontaine's run....
</P>
<P>
   Jones plays himself as a 1972 broadcaster _ and looks remarkably
like himself a quarter of a century later....
</P>
<P>
   And why couldn't Jones miscall this race and let Pre win (or did
we give away a key element to non-sports moviegoers)?...
</P>
<P>
   Memo to Def Master Shaq: Practicing free throws during the
lockout is good, trying to sell rap CDs in Bakersfield is bad.
That's bad in a bad way....
</P>
<P>
   Irony definition No. 6,262: Because of the season he's had, Mark
McGwire is about the most valuable player the game of baseball has
right now. But he won't win his league's most valuable award....
</P>
<P>
   Reason you didn't get to see McAndro try to one-up two-timin'
Sammy Sosa in the home-run twist was 'cuz this was one of the
``Sunday Night Baseball'' games ESPN wanted to ship over to ESPN2
so it could televise that huge ``Sunday Night Football'' New
England-Indianapolis tilt, but baseball's all-knowin' suits
wouldn't allow the swap. So the game dropped all together from
national view....
</P>
<P>
   Couldn't force-feed me a Big Mac even if it was on special for
.062 cents....
</P>
<P>
   Roll out the follicle carpet, Marv Albert goes back to work
today....
</P>
<P>
   Don't be so sure Murdoch had nuthin' to do with the U.S. Open
men's finals....
</P>
<P>
   Ross Porter obscure stat of the week: Eric Karros is the
major-league leader in career homers without a grand slam. He's
sittin' on 176....
</P>
<P>
   Upside to the huge expansion fee charged to the new suckers of
the Cleveland Browns _ Georgia Frontiere will receive NO SHARE of
it. When the Rams left L.A. for St. Louie in '95, Frontiere had to
forfeit the cut she'd usually get for the next two expansion teams
over a 10-year period _ unless a team was given to L.A. Even more
reason to hold off on begging for a new franchise....
</P>
<P>
   Attention fantasy dweebs: The latest McGwire-covered Sporting
News determines the top 100 players today in the NFL. The USC
grad-count is just four _ Tony Boselli, Junior Seau, Bruce Matthews
and Willie McGinest _ because it decided against including Keyshawn
``Just Put Me On the Damn List'' Johnson and purposely removed
Jason Sehorn after his season-ending knee injury. UCLA is
represented by three _ Troy Aikman, Jonathan Ogden and Carnell Lake
But don't rush out and get Aikman in any transactions today....
</P>
<P>
   Reggie White, who had three sacks Sunday, didn't make the list.
But we're OK with that....
</P>
<P>
   Hustler magazine publisher Larry Flint expands his literary
empire in March with a new golf lifestyle magazine called Backspin.
Flint tells Media Week: ``We want it to... have somewhat of an
attitude and hopefully not be as boring as those that are out
there.'' What could Flint possibly know about fore-play?...
</P>
<P>
   The Mets woulda started Hideous Nomo in today's game against the
Astros, 'cept they need a win....
</P>
<P>
   Apparently, Bret Saberhagen can afford to play big-league ball
three more years....
</P>
<P>
   Boxing has nuthin' to worry about. Except trying to sell this
weekend's fashion shows featuring Oscar De La Hoya and Evander
Holyfield, who will only be required to come down the runway, wink,
turn cheek and collect the check....
</P>
<P>
   And puleeeze don't forget to save up now for the _ e'gads _
Foreman-Holmes farce in January. Providing both are still living
past the first of the year....
</P>
<P>
   And the washed-up group KISS wants to hold a concert Halloween
night at Dodger Stadium. Let's check out schedule.... yes, that's
an open date. We also have available Sept. 28, 29, 30....
</P>
<P>
   Get Bob Costas off my Emmy telecast right now.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
