<P>
   NIRELAND-CHANGE (Dundalk, Ireland) _ Optimism is a sudden
newcomer to the North, but it's getting a warm welcome. People are
daring to put their frequently battered faith in a political
solution to the tribal conflict that has cost more than 3,200
lives, and there are convincing signs of cooperation in Belfast
between leaders of the warring Catholic and Protestant communities
who have battled and shunned one another for generations. By Warren
Hoge.
</P>
