FOSSILIZED SHOOTING STARS Tiny visitors from space (microscopic
meteorites entombed in rocks in Finland 1,400 million years ago,)
have the power to unlock secrets of Earth's ancient past. By Henry
Gee. Nature News Service. 600 words. (N/A France and Spain.) 
