perhaps even vastly different perceptions of Hollywood moviemaking,
Mazzello's and Smith's comments about the making of ``Simon Birch''
reflect their individual approaches to acting as much as they
reveal Mazzello's veteran status in Hollywood and Smith's role as
the enthusiastic newcomer. (Macor, Austin American-Statesman)
