<P>
   &UR; THE BABY WHO STOPPED EATING &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (1,600 words) &QL; 
 &UR; ONE COLOR ILLUSTRATION &QL; 
 &UR; By ROBERT MARION &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   Robert Marion, a professor of pediatrics at Albert Einstein
Medical College and director of the Center for Congenital Disorders
at Montefiore Medical Center in New York, reports on his treatment
of an infant patient who one day for no apparent reason stopped
nursing. The answer was found in a jar of honey.
</P>
<P>
   SLUGGED: BC-BABY-WON'T-EAT-NYTSF
</P>
