</P>
<P>
   IRAQ-PARLIAMENT (United Nations) _ The Iraqi Parliament, a
rubberstamp but predictive body on future government behavior,
calls on the Security Council to rescind its actions suspending
sanctions reviews or face a complete cutoff of cooperation with
even long-term weapons monitoring. By Barbara Crossette.
</P>
<P>
   NIRELAND-ASSEMBLY (Belfast) _ The new Northern Ireland Assembly
holds its first working session. By James F. Clarity.
</P>
<P>
   INDONESIA-PROTEST (Jakarta) _ Indonesian students press the
government to make sweeping changes in the role of the military,
with nearly 200 students staging a sit-down protest in one of the
capital's busiest thoroughfares.
</P>
