complicated by President Clinton's visit here for a speech and for
a fundraiser. By Adam Nagourney. (1300 words)
</P>
<P>
   WALLACE-ALABAMA (Dateline tk, Ala.) _ On the end of an era in
Alabama with the death of George Wallace. We talk to politicians
and historians, but also to the sort of ordinary people who once
put him in office to see how they feel now. Just as Wallace himself
had changed, so has the state of Alabama. By Rick Bragg.
