<P>
   POSTHUMOUS-BOOKS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ After publication of ``The Garden of Eden'' in 1986,
we supposed we had heard the last from Ernest Hemingway. But no.
Now we're told that Scribner will publish ``Truth at First Light,''
a novel believed to contain more comedy than Papa's usual quotient,
in the summer of 1999, as part of a Hemingway centennial
celebration. The factual/fictional account follows a writer and his
wife on an African safari. By LARRY SWINDELL. Story will move in
``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BOOKTV &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ At first glance, TV shows about books seem like an
oxymoron. But the low-tech, intellectual book programs on C-SPAN2
have grown so popular that the cable channel launched ``Book TV,''
devoting every weekend to shows about books and the book industry.
By JEFF GUINN. Story will move in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
