 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    The Meryl Streep File
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Born: June 22, 1949, Summit, N.J.
</P>
<P>
   Real name: Mary Louise Streep.
</P>
<P>
   Education: Vassar College and Yale University.
</P>
<P>
   First film role: A small part in ``Julia,'' 1977.
</P>
<P>
   Family: Husband Don Gummer, children Henry, Mary Willa, Grace
and Louisa. They live in northwest Connecticut, ``in the boonies,''
in Streep's words.
</P>
<P>
   Upcoming roles: The voice of the queen in ``Antz,'' Kate in
``Dancing at Lughnasa'' and a violin teacher in ``50 Violins.''
</P>
