<SLUG> BC-STREEP-LIST-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Must-See Meryl: Streep on video
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   -- ``The Deer Hunter.'' She won her first Oscar nomination as
Robert de Niro's small-town girlfriend in Michael Cimino's Vietnam
epic.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Kramer vs. Kramer.'' Winning the Oscar as Dustin Hoffman's
wife, battling for child custody.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Manhattan.'' A cameo as Woody Allen's acerbic, lesbian
ex-wife.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The French Lieutenant's Woman.'' Playing two roles: A
melancholy 19th-century social outcast, and the 20th-century
actress playing the role in the film of John Fowles' novel.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Sophie's Choice.'' Winning the Oscar for her devastating
turn as a Polish Holocaust survivor still warring with her painful
memories.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Silkwood.'' As real-life blue collar nuclear plants worker
Karen Silkwood, whose whistler-blowing led to major trouble.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Plenty.'' Lashing out at friends and lovers as a British
woman disenchanted by the status quo of England after the war.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Out of Africa.'' Growing coffee and falling in love with
Robert Redford as Danish writer Isak Dinesen.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Heartburn.'' Falling in love with charismatic, womanizing
Jack Nicholson in Nora Ephron's autobiographical comedy.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``A Cry in the Dark.'' Losing her baby to a dingo, then
facing national suspicion that she killed him in Peter Weir's
Australian drama.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Death Becomes Her.'' Competing for the comic vanity trophy,
playing a faded Hollywood actress opposite Goldie Hawn in Robert
Zemeckis' black comedy.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The River Wild.'' Meryl plays action hero in this
white-water thriller, directed by Curtis Hanson (``L.A.
Confidential'').
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The Bridges of Madison County.'' Tumbling into a
bittersweet, adulterous liaison with photographer Clint Eastwood in
the film of the popular book.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Marvin's Room.'' Playing mom to juvenile delinquent
Leonardo DiCaprio in this family comedy-drama with Diane Keaton.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
