<P>
   &QL; 
HERITAGE (Phoenix) - Marcy Gorman points to a slice of Arizona
history. A modest four-room adobe home built 106 years ago, where a
pioneer laid down roots, raised a family and tilled the land. But
unlike other frontiersmen, this one didn't make his way to Arizona
from Eastern lands. He came through Mexico and represents a fact
many people fail to realize: Hispanics were among Arizona's first
settlers.
</P>
<P>
   Today, Latinos around the country begin celebrating National
Hispanic Heritage Month, which runs from Sept. 15 to Oct. 15. It is
a time for Hispanics to honor their past and educate others about
the diversity of their culture and their place in American society.
By JULIE AMPARANO. Story will move in the ``A`` category. &QL; 
