expected. However, Arizona is still third in the nation for
creating new jobs. By CATHERINE REAGOR. Story will move in the
``F'' category. &QL; 
CONDORS (Undated) - Arizona will host more California condors than
California when nine more of the endangered giant vultures are
released at a second site north of the Grand Canyon _ the Hurricane
Cliffs. The release of additional condors - the fourth such release
in Arizona since 1996 - is tentatively set for late November or
early December. It will bring Arizona's total to 24 birds, four
more than exist in the wild in California. By STEVE YOZWIAK. Story
will move in the ``A`` category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
