loudly and quickly and hung up before I could answer his question,
which was: ``Hey, moron, what kind of sick lesson do YOU think this
putrid Clinton scandal is teaching our children?'' There isn't one
lesson being taught, but many. For example, children might learn
that many of our most opinionated citizens choose to speak
anonymously into telephones. E.J.MONTINI. Story will move in the
``A'' and ``K'' categories. &QL; 
