<HEADLINE>
DUSTED WITH BEADS  
(JT)
</HEADLINE>
   By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO    
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ It may have started with Voyage, or possibly Narciso
Rodriguez, this tendency to decorate a basic sweater, but by now it
has taken hold at many price levels. The latest versions, which
bear little relation to your mother's heavily beaded sweater from
the '50s, have a tracing of beads around the neck or a delicate
spattering down the front, so they can go out by day or night.
</P>
<P>
   Beaded sleeveless pullovers by Rodriguez are $650 at Barneys New
York, which also has Rebecca Taylor's pullover ($165), tank ($135)
and cardigan ($175), and Urchin's camisole ($110) and cardigan
($150), all with beading at the neck.
</P>
<P>
   Henri Bendel has bead-edged cardigans ($218 and $318) and a
bead-spattered cardigan ($358) with a matching camisole ($158), all
by Luna B, and a short-sleeved bead-dotted cardigan ($168) and
matching tube ($88) by William B.
</P>
<P>
   Chloe's bead-trimmed camisole ($220) and cardigan ($340) and
Rebecca Moses' sleeveless pullover with tracings of beadwork down
the front ($880) are all at Bergdorf Goodman.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-14-98 2048EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
