<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
OREGON STATE'S ROOTS RUN DEEPLY INTO USC
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Oregon State might be overwhelmed by USC from the
standpoint of talent, but the Beavers will certainly be more
familiar with the Trojans than any other team on their schedule.
</P>
<P>
   Head coach Mike Riley was USC's offensive coordinator for four
seasons, but he's far from the only connection to the Trojans
football program. Riley also hired former USC assistant Mark Banker
in 1996 to coach the secondary last season.
</P>
<P>
   And he's added a couple more Trojans recently. Beavers defensive
line coach Jeff McInerney spent two seasons at USC before being
fired after John Robinson was dismissed. Oregon State video
coordinator Mark Preto left USC last spring after refusing to
accept a demotion; he was eventually hired by Riley over the
summer. Preto had been USC's video coordinator for three years.
</P>
<P>
   __ Quarterback derby?: USC coach Paul Hackett had only good
things to say about his quarterbacks, although sophomore Mike Van
Raaphorst seems entrenched as the starter _ for now.
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought Mike was a week better,'' Hackett said of the
Trojans' win over San Diego State. ``I thought Carson did some good
things. He made a silly throw. He showed poise. He's got a presence
about him.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Drought in L.A.: Oregon State has not defeated USC in Los
Angeles since 1960, which was John McKay's first season. The
Beavers have lost 24 straight games to USC, a Pacific-10 record.
Oregon State last defeated the Trojans in 1967.
</P>
<P>
   Oregon State is winless in the Pac-10 since 1996 and last won a
conference road game in 1994, when it upset UCLA.
</P>
<P>
   __ Gibson honored: Linebacker David Gibson was named Pac-10
defensive player of the week for his performance against San Diego
State. Gibson had eight tackles, forced three fumbles, recovered a
fumble and sacked the quarterback three times.
</P>
<P>
   Gibson also won the honor last year after the Trojans' victory
over Oregon.
</P>
<P>
   __ Injury update: It appears Eric Denmon could be out for a
while with a sprain high in his ankle. Denmon is officially listed
as questionable, but he is wearing a boot on his ankle, which
usually means more than one week off. Linebacker Mark Cusano
(sprained ankle) is probable, although he might not practice every
day.
</P>
<P>
   __ Good start: If the Trojans defeat Oregon State, they will be
3-0 for the first time since 1995 and 3-0 for the just the third
time since 1988.
</P>
<P>
   __ Rushing totals: With its 232 yards rushing, USC moved up to
47th overall in the NCAA team-rushing statistics. Last week, the
Trojans ranked 69th. The Trojans ranked 111th out of 112 Division
I-A teams after two games last season.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
