<P>
   SCI-MULLIS-DNA (Undated) _ Kary Mullis won the Nobel Prize for
his inventions known as the polymerase chain reaction or PCR, used
for amplifying chosen sections of DNA. It has quickly become an
essential tool for biologists, DNA forensics labs, and almost
anyone else who needs to study the genetic material. But science
has been just one of the keen interests in Mullis's life, competing
with psychedelic drugs and women. Nowadays he is pursuing his
writing and venting his contempt for corrupt science in his highly
unorthodox ways. By Nicholas Wade.
