<P>
   SCI-NURSE-STUDY (Undated) _ More than 20 years ago, a doctor
curious about the effects of long-term oral contraceptive use sent
questionnaires to 370,000 registered nurses. The answers he and
colleagues have since received have turned into the largest and
longest study ever of a group of women. This massive scientific
effort has only begun to pay dividends. With many of the original
participants now entering their 60s and 70s, the study promises to
bequeath an even greater wealth of knowledge, much of it otherwise
unattainable, about how a lifetime of choices in food, drink,
exercise and medications can translate into protection from or
increased risk of deadly and debilitating diseases. By Carol Kaesuk
Yoon.
