</P>
<P>
   New York and Connecticut will hold primary elections Tuesday for
Democratic nominations for some statewide offices. There are
primaries in both the Democratic and Republican parties for some
district elections. The polls in New York will be open from 6 a.m.
to 9 p.m., and in Connecticut from 6 a.m. to 8 p.m. The following
are our recommendations in some of these races. All the district
contests involve Democrats in areas where nomination is tantamount
to election.
